## Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Example |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Module (directory) | `snake_case`, domain description | `tab_content`, `smart_data_grid` |
| Single file module | `snake_case`, domain description | `titlebar.rs`, `sidebar.rs` |
| Struct/Enum | `UpperCamelCase` | `SqlEditorTab`, `TabInfo` |
| Primary Struct File | `snake_case` of the struct | `sql_editor_tab.rs`, `grid_state.rs` |
| Grouped Items File | `snake_case`, group description | `output_content.rs`, `grid_error.rs` |
| Trait | `UpperCamelCase` | `TabItem`, `TableDelegate` |
| Parent Module (infra vs impl) | Infra = `tab/`, Impl = `tab_content/` | `tab/` ‚âÝ `tab_content/` |

---

## File Separation Rules

### When to separate files?

| Condition | Action |
| --- | --- |
| File > 300 lines | Consider moving sub-components to separate files |
| File > 500 lines | **MANDATORY** separation (excluding main entry points) |
| Impl block > 200 lines | Consider moving helper functions to a dedicated module |
| Multiple helper structs/enums | Move them to their own files |

### Exceptions ‚Äî separation not required

* `workspace.rs` (~200-300 lines): The main entry point for the workspace, containing action handlers.
* `connection_window.rs` (~400 lines): Dialogs where logic is tightly coupled with the UI.
* Files containing **only struct definitions** (< 50 lines, no impl blocks).

---

## Import Patterns

### Cross-module imports

```rust
// Inside workspace.rs ‚Äî importing from panel
use crate::panel::sidebar::Explorer;
use crate::panel::tab::tab_bar::TabBar;
use crate::panel::tab::tab_manager::TabManager;
use crate::panel::titlebar::Titlebar;

// Inside sidebar.rs ‚Äî opening a new tab
use crate::panel::tab_content::sql_editor::sql_editor_tab::SqlEditorTab;
use crate::panel::tab_content::table_viewer::table_viewer_tab::TableViewerTab;

```

### Reducing import length with `pub use`

```rust
// panel/tab_content/mod.rs ‚Äî high-level re-export
pub use sql_editor::sql_editor_tab::SqlEditorTab;
pub use table_viewer::table_viewer_tab::TableViewerTab;

// Then, in sidebar.rs:
use crate::panel::tab_content::SqlEditorTab;  // Much cleaner!

```

---

## Comparison with Engine Crate

| Rule | Engine | Desktop |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `mod.rs` re-export only | ‚úÖ Mandatory | ‚úÖ Mandatory |
| `pub mod` vs `mod` | `mod X;` (private) | `mod X;` (it's an app, no exports) |
| `pub use` | Needed to export to crate root | Internal only (shortens paths) |
| Single file module | ‚úÖ | ‚úÖ |
| File size limit | ~500 lines | ~300 lines (Render code is verbose) |
| Maximum depth | 2 levels | 4 levels |

---

## Specific Modules

### `action.rs` ‚Äî GPUI Actions Pattern

This file **does not follow** the `mod.rs` rule because it uses GPUI's `actions!()` macro to define actions. This is a specific pattern required by the GPUI framework:

```rust
pub mod toolbar {
    use gpui::actions;
    actions!(toolbar, [NewDatabase, OpenFile, UseInMemory]);
}

```

### `theme/mod.rs` ‚Äî Free Functions Pattern

This module contains only **free functions** (`init`, `change_theme`, `toggle_dark_light`) and no main struct. This is an acceptable pattern for utility modules.

### `connection/` ‚Äî Service Layer

This module contains only **services/state**, no GPUI Views. There is no need for view separation as it only contains models and stores.

---

## Pre-commit Checklist

* [ ] All `mod.rs` files contain only `mod X;` + `pub use X::*;` (no logic).
* [ ] File name = snake_case of the primary struct.
* [ ] No file exceeds 500 lines (except entry points).
* [ ] Maximum depth is 4 levels from `src/`.
* [ ] Import paths are clear; avoid `use super::*;` unless absolutely necessary.
* [ ] Each module has a single clear responsibility (no "god modules").
